<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/19899037-trevor"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1425174307i/19899037._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/19899037-trevor">Trevor</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">From my perspective, he is and also isn&apos;t at the same time. He compromised witness&apos; identities and he manipulated suspects to giving in to confess. Th<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">From my perspective, he is and also isn't at the same time. He compromised witness' identities and he manipulated suspects to giving in to confess. There's no doubt that he did some shady stuff. But also, I think most of those acts were in for justice and finding a murderer and providing closure to a family that lost their kid. It really depends on if you think what he did was justified or not. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
